     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="87"/>
   <head>To his Friend the Authour.</head>
   <l>SOmetimes (deare friend) I make thy Booke my meat,</l>
   <l>And then I iudge 'tis <hi>Hony</hi> that I eat.</l>
   <l>Sometimes my drinke it is, and then I thinke</l>
   <l>It is <hi>Apollo's Nectar,</hi> and no drinke.</l>
   <l>And being hurt in minde, I keepe in store</l>
   <l>Thy Booke, a precious <hi>Balsame</hi> for the sore▪</l>
   <l>'Tis <hi>Hony, Nectar, Balsame</hi> most diuine:</l>
   <l>Or one word for them all; my Friend, 'tis thine.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>
         <hi>THO. HEYGATE,</hi> è Societate Inter. Templi.</signed>
   </closer>
